<div class='download-page'>
  <h2 class='container'>Download Data</h2>
  <div class='prose container'>Here you can download the complete Global Adaptation Index 1.0 (GaIn 1.0). This includes the final scores, but also the raw data, all interpolations and partial scores. Data comprises all 192 UN countries (as of Dec. 2010), 15 years (from 1995 to 2010), all 35 Indicators and each computational step (Raw sourced data, Interpolated value to fill data gaps where possible, and Score values). Roughly half a million numbers. Data is provided in separate CSV files. It includes:</div>
  <ul>
    <li>Global Adaptation Index.</li>
    <li>Vulnerability score.</li>
    <li>Vulnerability sector scores: Water, Agriculture, Health, Infrastructure.</li>
    <li>Component scores: Exposure, Sensitivity, Capacity.</li>
    <li>Readiness score.</li>
    <li>Readiness sector scores: Economic Readiness, Governance, Social Readiness.</li>
    <li>GDP adjusted scores for GaIn, Vulnerability and Readiness scores.</li>
    <li>All 35 indicators used to generate GaIn.</li>
    <li>Additional context information (Populations and GDP)</li>
  </ul>
  <a href='/assets/gain/files/<%= model.escape('filename') %>' class='container button green'>
      DOWNLOAD (.zip, <%= model.getFileSize() %>)
      <span class='timestamp'>Last updated on <%= model.getDate() %></span>
  </a>
  Terms of use: <a class='ccbadge container' href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/3.0/">Attribution 3.0 Unported</a>
</div>
